'Some people, like DK and me, have good grammar.'

' Some people, like I, have good grammar.'
Ergo, 'and me' is grammatically correct in this sentence."




You are welcome. :-)

snippet.textDisplay:
I had a really good laugh this video, so I thought I would just put this out there for you guys. I found Team Edge back when it was just Matt, Bryan, and Joey. I was always feeling depressed, but you guys just made me laugh so much that I fell in love with this channel. I binge watched all of your videos after that, and you guys still continue to make me happy. My depression is getting worse (not saying this for attention, only for context), and I haven't had really good laughs and stuff recently. But I almost just cried from laughing so much, I was taken back by my laughing tbh.

I just wanted to say that I love you guys, and thank you for making not just me, but all of us laugh and have good times, especially when we need it. c: <3
